</div>
<p>As we can see with the map, the darker colored states equate to a higher murder/100k people. Some obvious patterns are that some of the higher murder numbers occur in states in the south, while the lighest colored states seem to be in New England and also in some of the sparsely populated states in the northern midwest.</p>
</section>
