<p>The map of assaults per 100k people has some similarities to the previous one. For starters, New England is extremely low yet again, and the northern midwest states are also very light colored. The southern states don’t seem quite as dark as the map on murders, and we can notice that two states, Colorado and New Mexico seem to stand out as being the most dark colored.</p>
